Description: Foot sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery cup (probably Type C); glazed black on exterior (streaky) and underside; reserved: outer face of foot and resting surface; foot slightly convex with low ridge at edge on top; resting surface convex with pair of slight tooled grooves; inscription cut on underside.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1600)
